1 TITL United Kingdom, Royal Navy RatingsŌĆÖ Service Records, 1853-1928
1 PUBL MyHeritage
1 TEXT An individual must have enlisted before 1929 to have a record within this collection. Some of the records cover periods of service up to at least 1950. Included in this collection are continuous servi
2 CONC ce engagement books from 1853 to 1872, registers of seamenŌĆÖs services from 1873 to 1924, registers of seamenŌĆÖs services from 1925-1928, and continuous record (CR) cards from 1929-1950. A record ma
2 CONC y indicate that the rating was promoted to warrant officer. The original records may contain the names of ships served on, with dates of joining and discharge from each ship, period of time actually s
2 CONC erved, any engagements not completed and the reason for noncompletion, service numbers (CS) up to 1872, and official numbers (ON) from 1873 onwards. Beginning in 1892 greater detail is included in the
2 CONC  records, such as: occupation, good conduct badges issued, notes made about character and ability, physical appearance, wounds suffered, and date of death (if occurred in service). The content in this
2 CONC  collection originates from The National Archives and contains public sector information licensed under the Open Government Licence v3.0.
